You can find the focus state‚Ä¶]]></description><link>https://easy-code.blog/chrome-debug-popup/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://easy-code.blog/chrome-debug-popup/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 06 Nov 2022 22:12:03 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;Most of the time they works, but when you have an issue with focus state it can be very frustrating to debug.
You can find the focus state in many components for example popup when you are hovering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;So, how to debug it?!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many ways to debug focus, but I found this one the easiest for me :)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open DevTools and place the breakpoint where you want to start.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to console tab and place the following code:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;js&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-js&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-js&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;setTimeout&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;debugger&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token number&quot;&gt;5000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol start=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to your Popup or View and hover it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(in case 5 seconds in not enough time, you can change it)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy Debugging üë®üèº‚Äçüíªüë©‚Äçüíª&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>